            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-23T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-23T09:00:00-05:00" n="1065" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1065">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W./11–2345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-23T15:00:00+01:00">November 23, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6757. From Angell No. 76.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Prewar claims against Germany. The Paris Conference on Reparation recommends
                        that reparation settlement not be considered as limiting the power of the
                        countries represented to negotiate with some future German Govt regarding
                        settlement of pecuniary claims against Germany arising out of contract and
                        other rights which preceded existence of a state of war between Germany and
                        the country concerned.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
